annotationA: Uridine 5'-monophosphate synthase; Orotidine-5'-phosphate decarboxylase activity; orotate phosphoribosyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: 'de novo' pyrimidine nucleobase biosynthetic process; 'de novo' UMP biosynthetic process; In the N-terminal section; belongs to the purine/pyrimidine phosphoribosyltransferase family
annotationB: Dihydroorotate dehydrogenase is a protein that is associated with the inner mitochondrial membrane. It catalyzes the fourth step of de novo pyrimidine biosynthesis, which is required for normal cuticle formation and oogenesis
